]},{"name":"Marye","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Maria .  When first introduced to England in the Middle Ages, it was Anglicized in pronunciation and respelled   Mary .  This French form was reintroduced into the English-speaking world as a separate name in the 19th century, and is still pronounced more or less in the French manner, although sometimes with the stress on the first syllable. It is now often used in combination with other names such as <i>Ellie</i>, <i>Chloe</i>, and <i>Lisa</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Marye Not was born in 1597, in England, United Kingdom, her father, John Wormall, was 23 and her mother, Sarah Wormall, was 20. She married William Land III on 1 August 1614, in Saint Dunstan and All Saints Church, Stepney, Middlesex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1667, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1597–1667":"1597–1667","1600–1661":"1600–1661","1634–1683":"1634–1683","1575–Male":"1575–Surnud","1578–Female":"1578–Surnud","1667":"1667","1634":"1634","1578":"1578","1600":"1600","1 August 1614":"1. august 1614","1597":"1597","before 30 November 1634":"enne 30. novembrit 1634","1575":"1575","1661":"1661","1683":"1683","01 AUG 1614":"1. august 1614","Dent, Yorkshire, England":"Dent, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Horbury, Yorkshire, England":"Horbury, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","St Dunstan and All the Saints, Stepney, Middlesex, England":"Saint Dunstan and All Saints Church, Stepney, Middlesex, England","Saint Dunstan,Stepney,London,England":"Stepney, London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1597–1667":"1597–1667","1600–1661":"1600–1661","1634–1683":"1634–1683","1575–Male":"1575–Kuollut","1578–Female":"1578–Kuollut","1667":"1667","1634":"1634","1578":"1578","1600":"1600","1 August 1614":"1. elokuuta 1614","1597":"1597","before 30 November 16